    162           1.  Firms
    163           2.  Commodity supply
    164           3.  Income distribution
    165           4.  Allocation of income across expenditure categories
    166           5.  Domestic final demand
    167           6.  Trade, goods market equilibrium and prices
    168           7.  Factor market equilibrium
    169           8.  Allocation of global saving
    170           9.  Tax revenue streams
    171          10.  Numeraire and Walras law
    172               ................................................
    173               Summary Indices (for use in welfare measurement)
    174               ................................................
    175               B-0. Variables and coefficients for summary indices
